parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light comes on
the vehicle pulls to one side or the other
the brakes lock up or fail to engage
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop
and the vehicle may skid or lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop
and the brakes may fail to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive brake pad wear can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pads wear out quickly
the vehicle pulls to one side or the other
and the brakes may vibrate or make noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corroded ABS sensors can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light comes on
the vehicle pulls to one side or the other
and the brakes may lock up or fail to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver seat frame can cause the seat to collapse or shift suddenly, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries. This is a critical safety issue, especially during sudden maneuvers or crashes.
symptoms: The driver seat feels unstable
rocks back and forth
or tilts to one side; the seat collapses or shifts suddenly; the seat frame breaks or cracks at the attachment points; the seat belt may not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper motor can cause the wipers to stop working or operate intermittently, leading to poor visibility during rainy or snowy weather, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windshield wipers stop working or operate intermittently
the wipers fail to turn on or off
the wipers stick or remain in a fixed position
the wipers work erratically
the wiper motor makes a strange noise or produces a burning smell.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The disconnection of the windshield wiper arm can cause the wiper to lose visibility, making it difficult to drive safely, especially during rainy or snowy weather.
symptoms: The windshield wiper arm disconnects while driving
the wiper arm rests on the side mirror or windshield
the driver loses visibility due to the disconnected wiper arm.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dealer to honor the recall can cause the consumer to be left with an unrepaired vehicle, which can lead to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: The dealer refuses to repair the vehicle under the recall
the dealer claims the vehicle is not included in the recall despite having the same defect
the dealer fails to provide reimbursement for repairs made prior to the recall.
